data.name: python-dotjson
data.description: python-dotjson helps you derive configuration using a settings.json file. You can choose to load the configuration in a flattened manner to your environment variables, You can also load the config to a Pydantic data model.

data.name: Secret Sharing API
data.description: Secret sharing API is a prototype for a Serverless DynamoDB-backed service that allows users to safely share secret strings across the network. The secret message self-destructs after the time to live has passed or if the message has been extracted once.

data.name: Dockerized Gitversion
data.description: GitVersion is a tool to help you achieve Semantic Versioning on your project. This image will run the GitVersion command-line tool inside a docker container and return a semantic version When included in a Multistage docker build.
